# 🔐 AWS IAM Hands-On Project

## 📌 Overview

This project demonstrates hands-on implementation of AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM).

The objective of this project was to understand how authentication and authorization work in AWS and how IAM helps secure cloud resources through users, groups, roles, and policies.

---

# 🚀 Services Used

* AWS IAM
* AWS Management Console
* AWS S3 (for permission testing)

---

# 📚 Concepts Learned

<details>
  <summary>🔑 Authentication vs Authorization</summary>

* Authentication verifies the identity of a user.
* Authorization controls what actions the user can perform.

Both are critical for securing AWS resources.

</details>

<details>
  <summary>👤 IAM Users</summary>

* Created IAM users
* Configured console access
* Enabled password reset on first login
* Tested secure login access

</details>

<details>
  <summary>👥 IAM Groups</summary>

* Created groups for easier permission management
* Added users into groups
* Managed permissions at group level instead of individual users

</details>

<details>
  <summary>📜 IAM Policies</summary>

* Attached AWS managed policies
* Explored custom policies using JSON format
* Learned:

  * Effect
  * Action
  * Resource

</details>

<details>
  <summary>🛡️ AWS Security Best Practices</summary>

* Avoid using root account for daily tasks
* Follow least privilege access
* Use groups for scalable permission management
* Control access carefully to prevent accidental changes

</details>

